Comment: The british grandmaster John Nunn is 51 years of age, but in the next game against the 21 year old dutch grandmaster Jan Smeets, he shows he can still play...Taken from the fourth round of the NH Chess tournament played at Hotel Krasnapolsky in the heart of Amsterdam.

Black clears the seventh row, so the queen can become involved in the defence. But there's more....

After the game Nunn showed the following amazing line: 
29...Bxc4 30.Bxc4 Nxe5 31.Re4 Ra-d8 32.Rh4 Rd1 33.Bf1 f6 34.Qh8  Kf7 
35. Rh7  Kg6 36.Nh4  Kg5 37.Rh5  Kf4 38.Qxf6  Ke4 39.Rxe5  Qxe5 40.Qf3  Kd4 41.Qxd1  Ke4 42.Qf3  Kd4 43.Qd3 mate! That's some deep calculating going on there :)
